Mid-Term Project¶

Overview¶

  • Use Medicare CCLF Claims from Syntegra dataset to answer key business questions
  • Extra credit for building up on the questions below (additional questions + answers)
  • One Jupyter notebook solution with clear Python code and all cell outputs available
  • At least two data quality checks
In [1]:
## Step 0. Prepare raw input datasets

Here we will 1) load original datasets, 2) remove unused columns, 3) de-duplicate rows, and 4) join datasets, not necessarily in this order

Assumptions:

  • Claim ID (cur_clm_uniq_id) represents one claim, which may or may not have more than one code (code could be HCPCS/CPT, diagnosis, procedure...)
  • There is a one-to-many relationship between patient IDs (bene_mbi_id) and claim IDs (cur_clm_uniq_id), i.e. each claim is unique to one patient, but one patient can have more than one claim

top_100_hcpcs_merged_df.loc[:, 'claim_year'] = top_100_hcpcs_merged_df['claim_year'].astype(int)
total_num_uniq_clm_by_year_df = top_100_hcpcs_merged_df.groupby('claim_year').agg(
    total_clm_count=('claim_id', 'nunique')
)
clm_count_by_year_cat_df = total_num_uniq_cardiac_clm_by_year_df.join(
    total_num_uniq_clm_by_year_df
)
clm_count_by_year_cat_df['other_clm_count'] = clm_count_by_year_cat_df['total_clm_count']-clm_count_by_year_cat_df['cardiac_clm_count']
clm_count_by_year_cat_df= clm_count_by_year_cat_df.astype(int)

    columns={
        'cardiac_clm_count': 'Cardiac',
        'other_clm_count': 'Other',
        'total_clm_count': 'Total'
    }
)

How would you determine which sales tactic is best for which segment?

From the Bar graph above we can infer that more HCPs are being associated with CVM related procedures. The HCP's number is growing at a CAGR of ~14% Sales Tactic for each bucket: For the Disease Aware segment which also constitues of the majority HCPs amongst 4 might require more nurturing and education about the producrs. Direct Sales force interaction might not work since these HCPs have lower level of engagement. Here the Best Approach would be to make Non-personal promotional(NPP) efforts like: emails, webinars and through social media. Also occasional visit from medical liasons might also be fruitful. Trialist : These HCps with 2-4 CVM claims suggests a primitive level of engagement. Hence a combination of NPPs and in-person sales force deplyemennt might be fruitful.In this case, in-person sessons will allow a deeper level of engagement followed by NPPs which will allow post-session follow-ups. Rising Stars : This segment indicates considerable level of interest and growing engagement. Also from the data we can infer that the numbers has shown a slight decline. Hence an aggresive Direct sales force engagement with more personalized approach can help in retention and amplificato of sales. High level Prescribers : These HCPs have highest level of engagement and has shown frequemt CVM related prescription behaviours. For this segment, dedicating in-person sales team and providing a more personalized support is crucial.

top_procedures_by_gender_unstacked = top_procedures_by_gender.unstack()
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

bar_width = 0.35  # Define bar width and positions for each group
index = range(len(top_procedures_by_gender_unstacked.columns))

# Plot bars for each gender
for i, (gender, color) in enumerate(zip(top_procedures_by_gender_unstacked.index, ['blue', 'orange'])):
    ax.bar([x + i * bar_width for x in index], top_procedures_by_gender_unstacked.loc[gender], bar_width, label=gender, color=color)

# Set labels and title
ax.set_xlabel('Procedure Description')
ax.set_ylabel('Count')
ax.set_title('Top Procedure Types by Gender')
ax.set_xticks([x + bar_width for x in index])
ax.set_xticklabels(top_procedures_by_gender_unstacked.columns)
ax.legend(['Female', 'Male'])

plt.show()

From the above analysis we can infer that the number of claims made by females are more than males in the top 5 categories.This information can be helpful in tailoring marketing strategies as per the segregation.¶

-Targeted campaings : These information can be used to develope tailored content and advertisement that resonate around gender's preferences. -Further research can be initiated to determine why claims by males are comparatively lesser in this categories.
